Topics in the alphabetical correspondence include: the
         Ramakrishna order and ecumenism (C: 1987 May 5, April 8,
         January 9 & 24; 1986 December 21 & 2, October 8, June
         22, May 5, and April 22; and G: 1986 June 9, May 26, Apr 14);
         Indian politics and anti-United States sentiment (B: 1987 June
         9, January 29; 1986 August 16, May 31; and P: 1986 June 15);
         Malachi Martin and his book concerning the Jesuits (D: 1987
         April 3); discussion of Henri Frederic Amiel's 
         Journal Intime(D: 1986 May 5);
         Special Olympics and the Kennedy family (D: 1986 January 4);
         South Africa (G: 1986 December 25, June 14); 
         Plains Poetry Journal(G: 1986
         February 23); Thomas Merton (H: 1986 August 12, May 17, April
         3); the Catholic Church and Pope Paul II (L: 1986 October 21);
         John Moffitt's conversion to Catholicism (Mc: 1987 June 6);
         Pol Pot (M: 1987 March 25); Cambodian refugees (M: 1986 Sep 23
         & 1, August 25, March 5); biographical information
         concerning John Moffitt (M: 1982 Sep 19); the Brazilian land
         situation (P: 1986 July 29); Vivekenanda (S: 1986 February 6);
         the United States bombing of Libya (T: 1986 May 27); United
         States foreign policy (T: 1986 February 23); the
         representative selection of Moffitt's poems entitled 
         Arrivings(1986 August 4);
         homosexuality and the Catholic Church (Z: 1986 November 29
         & 17); and Jiddu Krishnamurti (Y: 1986 March 3).
